{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013z2nSh1vteikTgUYK6Gqzd","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tA CockroachDB cluster is running v23.2 binaries and is ready for a major upgrade.\n2\t\n3\tYour task:\n4\tUpgrade the cluster to v24.1.0 and finalize the major upgrade.\n5\t\n6\tRequirements:\n7\t- Upgrade binaries first, then finalize the major upgrade.\n8\t- Keep the cluster available throughout.\n9\t\n10\tUseful commands:\n11\t```bash\n12\tkubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\n13\tkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n14\t```\n15\t\n16\tVerification:\n17\t1. All pods on v24.1.0:\n18\t   kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n19\t\n20\t2. Cluster version finalized:\n21\t   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n22\t     ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n23\t   (Should show '24.1' not '23.2')\n24\t\n25\t3. Preserve downgrade option cleared:\n26\t   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n27\t     ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n28\t   (Should show empty)\n29\t\n30\t4. Cluster healthy after finalization:\n31\t   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n32\t     ./cockroach node status --insecure\n33\t\n34\t5. Can use v24.1 features:\n35\t   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n36\t     ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SELECT version();\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8ce6b5c-f086-4831-91ef-f977822473ab","uuid":"90506001-be28-4dc7-97cd-0f9dfb20a521","timestamp":"2026-06-17T00:19:31.409Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/runs/error-prone-examples/cockroachdb-tls-upgrade-zone-audit-rollback-change-plan-20260616_235904/stages/stage_02/prompt.txt","content":"A CockroachDB cluster is running v23.2 binaries and is ready for a major upgrade.\n\nYour task:\nUpgrade the cluster to v24.1.0 and finalize the major upgrade.\n\nRequirements:\n- Upgrade binaries first, then finalize the major upgrade.\n- Keep the cluster available throughout.\n\nUseful commands:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n```\n\nVerification:\n1. All pods on v24.1.0:\n   kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n\n2. Cluster version finalized:\n   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n     ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n   (Should show '24.1' not '23.2')\n\n3. Preserve downgrade option cleared:\n   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n     ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n   (Should show empty)\n\n4. Cluster healthy after finalization:\n   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n     ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n5. Can use v24.1 features:\n   kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n     ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SELECT version();\"","numLines":36,"startLine":1,"totalLines":36}}}
