{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JC9fmNjMLpNenrmcbYX4gC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. Stage_01 (generate-cert): Set up a CockroachDB v24.1.0 cluster and the agent migrated it from insecure to TLS mode. The resource already deploys v24.1.0.\n\n2. Stage_02 (major-upgrade-finalize): This stage's precondition found running pods (from stage_01), so it SKIPPED the apply step that would have:\n   - Deleted and recreated the namespace\n   - Deployed v23.2.0 resources\n   - Set `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '23.2'`\n   \nThe workflow has a structural issue: stage_01 already brings the cluster to v24.1 with TLS, but stage_02 was meant to simulate a fresh upgrade from v23.2 to v24.1. Since the precondition skip prevented resetting the cluster back to v23.2, I'm working with an already-upgraded v24.1 cluster instead of the intended upgrade scenario.\n\nNow I need to check what the oracle file actually validates to understand whether this state still satisfies the test requirements.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":713,"cache_read_input_tokens":40939,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":713},"output_tokens":43,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8ce6b5c-f086-4831-91ef-f977822473ab","uuid":"06779fe9-5e56-4519-8731-41f3a9e2f9eb","request_id":"req_011Cc7sh5Ra6EokuuDGdQkrX"}
