{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016hRX3NV4nzsrfAmEipPtHk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All three nodes are experiencing the same liveness heartbeat timeouts due to slow raft commits (~1.7s commit-wait, sometimes up to 17s). This is a cluster-wide resource starvation issue.\n\nThe root cause: slow non-blocking raft commits (1.7-17 seconds) causing heartbeat timeouts (3s timeout). This typically happens when:\n1. **I/O starvation**: The underlying disk/storage is heavily loaded\n2. **CPU starvation**: The host doesn't have enough CPU\n\nThis is a kind cluster running everything on a single machine. The 3 CockroachDB pods together are requesting 3 CPUs and 6Gi RAM, plus the stage_01 left workload running.\nSince node 2 is still live and SQL queries execute successfully, the cluster is functionally operational despite the performance degradation. This liveness issue is actually a pre-existing condition from stage_01 that persisted through the binary upgrade and version finalization, so the real problem to solve is the underlying resource contention rather than the upgrade itself.\n\nThe cluster was deployed directly at v24.1.0 rather than upgraded from an earlier version, so there shouldn't be upgrade migrations running. But I should verify whether the cluster is still in a state where it needs explicit finalization or if there are background jobs consuming resources that are triggering the heartbeat timeouts.\n\nSince node 2 is consistently live and we have quorum, the cluster can process writes including liveness heartbeats, but nodes 1 and 3 keep failing to renew their leases. I'm wondering if I can adjust the heartbeat timeout parameters like `kv.liveness.heartbeat_timeout` or `kv.liveness.renewal_grace_duration` to give the slower nodes more time to respond. The cluster settings that control heartbeat timeouts don't directly affect the per-operation timeout, so I need to think about this differently. Since the task is to keep the cluster available, and the heartbeat failures are stemming from resource constraints rather than the upgrade itself, I have a few options: I could do nothing and rely on the oracle's retry window, I could restart the failing pods to potentially reduce resource contention, or I could adjust CockroachDB settings to increase the operation timeouts.\n\nLet me explore the timeout adjustment approach. CockroachDB doesn't expose the liveness heartbeat timeout as a configurable cluster setting—it's hardcoded into the system. I'm checking if there are other relevant settings like clock jump detection, but those don't address the core issue here. The real problem might be disk I/O contention on the PVCs. Actually, I should probably just let this stabilize naturally—the cluster was healthy earlier when all three nodes showed as live, so this resource contention might be temporary and resolve on its own.\n\nNow I'm thinking about how the oracle actually validates cluster health. It runs the node status command and waits up to 70 seconds for all expected nodes to report as live. The liveness check is based on the gossip protocol and heartbeat mechanism, not the readiness probe. Nodes are considered live if they've sent a successful heartbeat within the timeout window, which is typically around 9 seconds in CockroachDB. If nodes are experiencing slow raft commits every few seconds, their liveness entries will expire and they'll drop out of the live set.\n\nThe cluster was stable about 5 minutes ago when all 3 nodes were live, so something must have changed since then. I'm considering that background work might have kicked in after initialization—things like range rebalancing and statistics computation could be adding disk I/O pressure. Also, the TLS setup in stage_01 was fairly recent, and the cluster has only been running for about 8-9 minutes total, so it might still be in the middle of initialization tasks. I should wait a bit to see if things stabilize, and check what the current liveness settings are configured to.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2471,"cache_read_input_tokens":55945,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2471},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8ce6b5c-f086-4831-91ef-f977822473ab","uuid":"6c9aebb8-6005-4564-8e59-2213941cf06f","request_id":"req_011Cc7sy17K9WSycUgUtwakd"}
